SOS 69069 SYSTEM OVERVIEW

This contract is a:

Non-financial, event-driven identity + agreement graph

It has 3 core layers:

Mint → interaction trace

Trust → structured agreement

Join → external validation

Everything else supports these.

---

🔹 1. BASIC TOKEN STATE

name, symbol, decimals

Static metadata

Not used for trading (no transfers exist)


---

totalSupply

Increases ONLY when mint happens

Each mint = +1 wei


---

balanceOf[address]

Tracks how much an address has received

Important:

Sender NEVER receives balance

Only receiver gets +1 wei



---

🔹 2. SEED SYSTEM (IDENTITY LAYER)

mapping(address => bytes32) seedOf

Links each address → a seed (identity)

Multiple addresses can share same seed


---

declareSeed(address origin)

👉 Action:

User assigns themselves to a seed

👉 How it works:

Seed = keccak256(origin)

No permission required

Any address can join any seed

👉 Effect:

Identity is created or joined


---

seedName[seed]

nameSeed(bytes32 name)

👉 Action:

Assign a name to a seed

👉 Rules:

Only an address WITH that seed can name it

👉 Effect:

Lightweight labeling (for UI / graph tools)


---

🔹 3. RANK SYSTEM (CORE METRIC)

mapping(bytes32 => int256) rank

👉 This replaces traditional balances at seed level

---

How rank changes:

In mint():

Sender seed → -1
Receiver seed → +1

---

Meaning:

Positive rank → receives more than sends

Negative rank → sends more than receives


---

Use:

Reputation scoring

Weight metric (off-chain)

Trust evaluation


---

🔹 4. ATOMIC MINT SYSTEM

mint(address to)

👉 MOST IMPORTANT FUNCTION

---

What it does:

1. Checks:

no ETH sent

valid address

daily mint limit


2. Prevents:

❌ self-mint (same seed → same seed)


3. Updates:

receiver balance += 1 wei

totalSupply += 1 wei


4. Updates rank:

sender seed → -1

receiver seed → +1


5. Emits:




Mint(from, to, fromSeed, toSeed)

---

Key rules:

1 transaction = 1 mint

1 mint = exactly 1 wei

Sender gets NOTHING

Receiver gets EVERYTHING


---

Daily limit:

86400 mints per address per day

---

_enforceMintLimit()

👉 Resets daily counter
👉 Ensures limit is not exceeded

---

🔹 5. TRUST SYSTEM (STRUCTURED AGREEMENT)

createTrust(...)

createTrust(
    targetAddress,
    name,
    contextHash,
    parentTrust,
    p1, p2, p3
)

---

What it does:

👉 Emits an agreement event

TrustCreated(...)

---

Parameters:

targetAddress → the subject of the trust

name → short label (bytes32)

contextHash → proof reference (invoice / contract / deal)

parentTrust → link to previous agreement

p1, p2, p3 → participants (max 3)


---

Important:

❌ NOT stored on-chain

✔ ONLY emitted as event


---

Meaning:

"I declare a structured agreement involving these participants"

---

🔹 6. JOIN SYSTEM (EXTERNAL VALIDATION)

createJoin(...)

createJoin(
    targetAddress,
    name,
    contextHash,
    parentJoin
)

---

What it does:

👉 Emits validation event:

JoinCreated(...)

---

Parameters:

targetAddress → what is being validated

name → label

contextHash → proof

parentJoin → history chain


---

Meaning:

"I externally confirm / validate something about this target"

---

Difference from Trust:

Trust Join

structured open
max 3 participants unlimited
internal agreement external validation


---

🔹 7. EVENT-ONLY GRAPH DESIGN

Critical design decision:

❌ No Trust stored

❌ No Join stored

✔ Only events


---

Result:

Blockchain stores:

History, not state

---

Why this matters:

Very low gas cost

Infinite scalability

No state corruption risk

Full reconstructable graph off-chain


---

🔹 8. PARENT LINKING SYSTEM

parentTrust

parentJoin

---

Purpose:

Build chains:

Trust → Trust → Trust
Join → Join → Join

---

Used for:

dispute history

agreement evolution

long-term traceability


---

🔹 9. ACCESS CONTROL MODEL

Who can call Trust / Join?

✔ ONLY addresses with a seed:

require(seedOf[msg.sender] != 0)

---

No roles enforced on-chain

👉 All interpretation is:

OFF-CHAIN

---

🔹 10. HARD PROTOCOL ENFORCEMENT

Enforced in code:

✔ No ETH:

receive() → revert

fallback() → revert

_noETH() in all functions


---

✔ No transfer:

No transfer function exists


---

✔ No allowance:

No approve / allowance mapping


---

✔ No burn:

totalSupply NEVER decreases


---

✔ No selfdestruct:

Not implemented


---

✔ No self-mint:

require(fromSeed != toSeed)

---

✔ Financial state only via mint:

Only mint updates balances


---

✔ Trust/Join:

Events only

No manipulation possible


---

